<P>
   BUSH-MCCAIN (Lansing, Mich.) _ Texas Gov. George W. Bush and
Arizona Sen. John McCain carry their high-pitched battle to
Michigan for two days of strenuous campaigning before the Tuesday
Republican primary. Bush seeks to protect his frontrunner status
and McCain hopes to convince voters they should repeat the state's
history of supporting anti-establishment candidates. By STEWART M.
POWELL.
</P>
