upward to the curving rim above the first balcony and made a face.
``There used to be cream-colored stucco there,'' he said through
the grimace, ``the kind of thing that some theater restorations go
in for, all prettified duck-egg blue and pink. You can't put the
dirty world that we put onstage into a place like that.''
</P>
<P>
   nn
</P>
<P>
   In place of the unlamented stucco, the design team put nothing,
leaving exposed the riveted cast-iron plating they uncovered from
the original construction. It was an approach they used around the
building, letting the past of the theater catch up with the present
