putting on 40 plays at two theaters in the West End, the Duke of
York's and the New Ambassadors. The plays included Conor
McPherson's ``Weir,'' David Hare's ``Via Dolorosa,'' Martin
McDonagh's ``The Leenane Trilogy'' and Mark Ravenhill's ``Shopping
and ...'' For its reopening, the Royal Court is staging a new play
by McPherson called ``Dublin Carol,'' which started previews last
week.
</P>
<P>
   Opening night was supposed to have been Jan. 7, but the project
fell behind schedule. With everything else appearing to come out so
well, how did that happen?, Tompkins was asked over the sound of
last-minute sawing and hammering.
</P>
<P>
   ``You know what they say about builders,'' he said. ``They like
to build.''
</P>
