r l BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRO     02-20 0687
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 Copyright 2000 San Francisco Chronicle 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; THE BUSHING OF AMERICA &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Prescott Bush &LR; , uncle to  &UR; George W. &LR; , told Talk magazine that
his brother and sister-in-law, &UR; George &LR;  and  &UR; Barbara &LR; , are ``staying
away'' from the presidential campaign. ``They don't want to get in
the position of saying something and then finding that it caused
concern.''
</P>
<P>
   The former first lady, however, told the magazine that her
husband is ``obsessed'' by the campaign.
</P>
<P>
   As to her family's place in American politics, ``Did you know
that one out of eight Americans is governed by a Bush?'' she asked.
``That ought to scare you!''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; PRESIDENTIAL POLITICS IN THE MOVIES &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``Wheel of Fortune'' host  &UR; Pat Sajak &LR; , a conservative
Republican, discusses Hollywood's portrayal of presidents in the
latest issue of Los Angeles magazine.
</P>
<P>
   The movie president, he says, is ``always the mushy liberal with
the heart of gold, and he cares, and then the antagonist is
generally the hard-nosed conservative senator who wants to set
babies out into the snow to freeze.
</P>
<P>
   ``Because, after all, only liberal Democrats really care about
hunger.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; GETTING HELP WITH SELF-EXPRESSION &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Hallmark's new line, ``Ties That Bind,'' is described as ``cards
for today's families and lifestyles.'' A selection, with Personals'
suggestions for appropriate use:
</P>
<P>
   - ``You've become someone very important in my life, and I
couldn't be more proud of you if you were my own son.'' ( &UR; Jerry &LR; 
 &UR; Lewis &LR;  _ see below _ to his own daughter.)
</P>
<P>
   - ``I'm sorry for the times I've taken my confusion or anger out
on you unfairly, and I thank you for giving me the time _ and space
_ to let our relationship grow at its own pace.'' ( &UR; Rudy  &LR; to
 &UR; Hillary &LR; .)
</P>
<P>
   - ``You and I share a special bond that comes from loving the
same wonderful person. Thank you for all you've done to make my dad
so happy.'' ( &UR; Chelsea &LR;  to  &UR; Monica &LR; .)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; PETA MOVES AGAINST LEATHER &LR;
</P>
<P>
   People for the Ethical Treatment of Animals held a San Francisco
press conference last week, starring  &UR; Chrissie Hynde &LR;  and featuring
a graphic video, decrying the cruel treatment of Indian cows whose
hides are turned into leather. San Francisco was the site of the
anti-leather campaign launch because the Gap, which is
headquartered here, sells many leather products
</P>
<P>
   After the conference, PETA was invited by Gap executive  &UR; Alan &LR; 
 &UR; Marks  &LR; to discuss itsconcerns. Marks said the company buys its
leather products from apparel factories; clothing labeled ``Made in
India'' may not be made of cows slaughtered there. The Gap issued a
statement saying, ``We expect apparel factories to source leather
from vendors that follow applicable laws and industry best
practices, including the humane treatment of animals.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; JERRY LIKES WOMEN &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Jerry Lewis &LR;  says that his statements about women being better
suited to baby-making than to comedy were ``misinterpreted.'' He
said that he doesn't like women doing obscene comedy, ``and to me,
women doing anything, especially comedy, are looked upon by me as
one of God's great miracles.''
</P>
<P>
   Lewis said the media had done his wrong, having had ``to trash
someone to make a deadline.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   - Air Canada doesn't have tourist class; it doesn't have
steerage.  &UR; Mike Harris &LR;  took home a souvenir boarding pass that
indicates, instead, ``Hospitality'' class.
</P>
<P>
   - The dictionary's story:  &UR; T.E. Higgins  &LR; found notes on a wild
party in his Webster's Collegiate. The spread: Whoredom to Wieldy
Wiener to Wild Sarsaparilla. And another story atop another Yellow
Page, as scouted by  &UR; Alex Behr &LR; : ``Tourists-Towing.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``Is there something wrong with appreciating beautiful women?
Don't we want people in public office who show signs of life? I am
what I am, and I make no bones about it.''
</P>
<P>
   -  &UR; Donald Trump  &LR; in a Gear magazine essay on the possibility of
his presidential candidacy, apparently written before he dropped
out of the race.
</P>
