<P>
   MICH-REPUBS (East Lansing, Mich.) _ As the bitter fight for the
Republican presidential nomination shifted to Michigan, Sen. John
McCain leveled scorching and sustained attacks on Gov. George W.
Bush's reform credentials, while his rival stayed upbeat and
campaigned as if he were already in the general election. By Frank
Bruni and Alison Mitchell.
