   MICH-VOTERS (Roseville, Mich.) _ With time, money, political
momentum and the Republican machine working against him, John M.
McCain is trying to corral an unlikely coalition of moderate
suburban Republicans and poor urban Democrats, along with feisty
blue-collar independents. But showing the confidence of a
frontrunner whose believes his core of support is secure, George W.
Bush signaled that he would compete for some of the same voters. By
James Bennett
