 &UR; LINUX:  &LR; For the average computer user, Linux isn't nearly as
friendly as its smiling penguin mascot suggests. But now,
proponents of the freely distributed operating system are stepping
up efforts to make it more inviting to non-geeks. Eazel, a Palo
Alto startup, is working with volunteer programmers around the
world to give Linux a new ``graphical shell'' _ a point-and-click
interface for managing files and folders.  &UR; BY &LR; 
